course_title: SELECTED TOPICS IN MGMT: Data Driven Decision Making
subject: COM

sections.description: Description: The goal of this course is to build student insights and skills in working with and interpreting data in order to make intelligent, fact-based business decisions. The course will focus on combining basic mathematics, logical reasoning and presentation skills to build models, develop KPIs and, most importantly, to interpret and ‘tell the story’ that may be hidden in data.  Much of the discussion and coursework will be analytical, requiring logical reasoning and clear presentation skills.

course_title: SELECTED TOPICS IN MGMT: Revitalizing Indigenous Economies
subject: COM

sections.description: Course description: Indigenous peoples always had thriving economies based on principles of sustainability and stewardship of land and resources.  Through colonization, regressive laws and policies, indigenous peoples were removed from their lands and resource that in turn devastated traditional economies. This course will explore how those laws and policies achieved that, and explore what barriers still exist for indigenous peoples in revitalizing their economies. Issues examined include access to financing, taxation, and the unique legal and business framework within which indigenous peoples must compete. Best practices and case studies from BC First Nations will be used to understand opportunities, how to develop viable economies, entrepreneurial initiatives and associated needed capacities in indigenous communities and in the case of thriving indigenous economies-growth strategies.  This class will also study various business models to maximize tax incentives available to First Nations.
